Description. Male ( Holotype , Maroantsetra, Madagascar , SMF 10552 ). Total length 10.64 . Carapace 3.40 long, 2.65 wide, light brown (
Fig. 21
); fovea marked (
Fig. 21
). Clypeus light brown, 0.12 high. Anterior eye row strongly procurved in frontal view (
Fig. 22
), 0.80 wide; posterior recurved in dorsal view (
Fig. 21
), 1.30 wide. Eye diameters, interdistances, and median ocular quadrangle: AME 0.18 , ALE 0.10 , PME 0.16 , PLE 0.20 ; AME-AME 0.10 , AME-ALE 0.24 , PME-PME 0.28 , PME-PLE 0.26 , OQA 0.46 , OQP 0.62 , OQH 0.46 . Chelicerae light brown with a few dark brown spots, glabrous (
Fig. 22
). Sternum dark brown with a median light brown band, with scattered setae; 1.66 long, 1.49 wide. Labium light brown, dark brown laterally; 0.41 long, 0.55 wide. Legs light brown, relative length: II-I-IV-III, I—femur 6.30 / patella-tibia 7.96 / metatarsus 6.31 / tarsus 3.07 / total 23.64 ; II— 6.47 / 8.13 / 6.47 / 3.23 / 24.30 ; III— 4.56 / 4.98 / 4.15 / 1.90 / 15.59 ; IV— 6.14 / 6.64 / 6.47 / 2.49 / 21.74 . Ventral pairs of macrosetae on tibiae:
