Abdomen 6.97 long, light brown with two paramedian white lines laterally (
Fig. 21
); with three pairs of dorsal sigillae. Venter light brown, with scattered setae. Male palpus with a robust and divided distal tegular apophysis, with an acute apex and with a short distal tegular projection ( Figs 19 ,
